    <item>
      <title>Guides: Overview: Resource groups</title>
      <link>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/operations/groups/overview/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://docs.radapp.io/guides/operations/groups/overview/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;Resource groups are collections of resources that you can manage as a single unit. You can use resource groups to organize your resources when deploying Radius Applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;group-diagram.png&#34; alt=&#34;Diagram showing Radius resources inside of a Radius resource group&#34; width=600px /&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-primary&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&#34;alert-heading&#34;&gt;Radius vs. Azure Resource Groups&lt;/h4&gt;

    Note that resource groups in Radius are not the same as &lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-resource-manager/management/manage-resource-groups-portal&#34;&gt;Azure resource groups&lt;/a&gt;. Azure resource groups are used to organize Azure resources, while Radius resource groups are used to organize Radius resources, such as applications, environments, portable resources, and routes. When you deploy a template that contains both, Radius resources route to the Radius resource group defined in your workspace, and Azure resources route to the Azure resource group defined in your &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/guides/operations/providers/&#34;&gt;cloud provider&lt;/a&gt;.

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;initialization&#34;&gt;Initialization&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of &lt;code&gt;rad init&lt;/code&gt;, a default resource group is created for you, with the same name as your environment. This resource group is set as the default &amp;lsquo;scope&amp;rsquo; of your &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/guides/operations/workspaces/&#34;&gt;workspace&lt;/a&gt;, so that all Radius resources you deploy will be created in this resource group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;manage-groups-with-rad-cli&#34;&gt;Manage groups with rad CLI&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rad CLI provides commands for managing resource groups. You can use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_group/&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;rad group&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; commands to create, list, and delete groups:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&#34;nav nav-tabs&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3&#34; role=&#34;tablist&#34;&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link active&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-3-create-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-3-create&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-3-create&#34; aria-selected=&#34;true&#34;&gt;
    create
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-3-list-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-3-list&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-3-list&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    list
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-3-show-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-3-show&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-3-show&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    show
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-3-delete-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-3-delete&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-3-delete&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    delete
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class=&#34;nav-item&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;nav-link&#34;
    id=&#34;tabs-3-switch-tab&#34; data-toggle=&#34;tab&#34; href=&#34;#tabs-3-switch&#34; role=&#34;tab&#34;
    aria-controls=&#34;tabs-3-switch&#34; aria-selected=&#34;false&#34;&gt;
    switch
  &lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-content&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-content&#34;&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade show active&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-create&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-3-create-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_group_create/&#34;&gt;rad group create&lt;/a&gt; creates a new resource group:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rad group create myrg
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-list&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-3-list-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_group_list/&#34;&gt;rad group list&lt;/a&gt; lists all of the resource groups in your Radius installation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rad group list
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-show&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-3-show-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_group_show/&#34;&gt;rad group show&lt;/a&gt; prints information on a resource group:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rad group show
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-delete&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-3-delete-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_group_delete/&#34;&gt;rad group delete&lt;/a&gt; deletes the specified resource group:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rad group delete -e mygroup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;tab-pane fade&#34; id=&#34;tabs-3-switch&#34; role=&#34;tabpanel&#34; aria-labelled-by=&#34;tabs-3-switch-tab&#34;&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_group_switch/&#34;&gt;rad group switch&lt;/a&gt; switches the default resource group in your &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/guides/operations/workspaces/&#34;&gt;workspace&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;rad group switch mygroup
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;additional-information&#34;&gt;Additional information&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/concepts/api-concept/&#34;&gt;Radius API&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/concepts/architecture/&#34;&gt;Radius architecture&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.radapp.io/reference/cli/rad_group/&#34;&gt;rad CLI reference&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

      </description>
